Site_Description:
&lt;span lang="EN-GB"&gt;The following production units can be
identified at the site, which makes auxiliary products for the textile industry
(ATECO code 20.59.60):&lt;br&gt;
Unit RS1, in which processing involving chemical synthesis is carried out;&lt;br&gt;
Unit RS2, where the main activities are mixing, formulation and very simple
synthesis reactions;&lt;br&gt;
Drying area, where products are put through a drying process for sale as powder
packed in sacks or big bags;&lt;br&gt;
Hydrolyser area â€” pilot plant PCl3, for the production of phosphoric acid and
hydrochloric acid from phosphorus trichloride.&lt;br&gt;
Connected to those facilities are numerous areas for the storage of raw
materials, production intermediates and finished products in above-ground
cylindrical tanks, drums or IBCs, appropriately separated and isolated, storage
warehouses for raw materials, intermediates and finished products in sacks or
drums, technical facilities, laboratories, offices and services.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%; font-family:" arial","sans-serif";mso-fareast-font-family:"times="" new="" roman";="" mso-ansi-language:it;mso-fareast-language:it;mso-bidi-language:ar-sa"=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;

